data-triple-N3.o: "The Pyrenees, also spelled Pyrenees, is a range of mountains in southwest Europe that forms a natural border between France and Spain. It separates the Iberian Peninsula from the rest of continental Europe, and extends for about 491km from the Bay of Biscay (Cap Higuer) to the Mediterranean. For the most part, the main crest forms a massive divider between France and Spain, with the tiny country of Andorra sandwiched in between."@en
